# Cloudflare Pages security headers for fluxtube.forklabs.cc.
#
# Format reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# Identical posture to forklabs.cc — both sites are siblings under the
# same apex, and direct-to-subdomain visitors need each Pages project to
# emit its own HSTS regardless of whether the apex includeSubDomains is
# active (HSTS only kicks in after the first HTTPS visit to the domain
# that emits it).
#
# Defaults Pages already sets (don't redeclare):
#   - x-content-type-options: nosniff
#   - referrer-policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
#   - HTTP → HTTPS 301 redirect
#
# Why each declared header — see forklabs-cc/public/_headers for the
# full reasoning. Key notes specific to this site:
#   - CSP allows google fonts + 'unsafe-inline' for both style/script.
#     Astro's `define:vars` injects inline style attrs; the terminal
#     type-in and countdown logic ships as small inlined <script> blocks.
#     Acceptable for a static marketing site with zero user input.
#   - The hosted OAuth callback page (/oauth/callback) does a JS
#     window.location.search parse + writes to the DOM, all from the
#     same origin. `script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'` covers it.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data:; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; connect-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
